The term's real gift: it reveals the default human assumption that life is chess and value https://t.co/YEE7OIicfe", "id_str": "2003540220352897031", "is_quote_status": false, "lang": "en", "possibly_sensitive": false, "possibly_sensitive_editable": true, "quote_count": 82, "reply_count": 327, "retweet_count": 725, "retweeted": false, "user_id_str": "386267766"}, "note_tweet": {"is_expandable": true, "note_tweet_results": {"result": {"entity_set": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwMDM1NDAyMjAyNzMxNDc5MDQ=", "media": {"inline_media": []}, "richtext": {"richtext_tags": []}, "text": "von Neumann gave us "zero-sum" in 1944 and it's one of my favorite examples of linguistic compression. Two words that mean “strictly competitive, fixed pie, stop looking for win-wins.”

The term's real gift: it reveals the default human assumption that life is chess and value can’t be created—only transferred. Once you have the label, you start noticing how often that’s wrong"}}}, "rest_id": "2003540220352897031", "source": "<a href="https://mobile.twitter.com" rel="nofollow">Twitter Web App</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "5342448", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}}, "rest_id": "2003579749176868875", "source": "<a href="http://twitter.com/download/iphone" rel="nofollow">Twitter for iPhone</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "5015129", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}

